stimulus:
In this experiment, you will answer questions about video clips showing moving billard balls.

The setting involves three balls labeled "Ball A", "Ball B", and "Ball E" correspondingly, and a red goal with goal posts as shown above.

Sometimes the goal is on the left side, and sometimes it's on the right side.

At some point the video clip will pause, and you will be asked to predict what will happen next. We won't give you feedback as to whether your prediction was right or wrong.

Notice that there is no friction in this setting. This means that balls don't slow down over time.

Click on the play button to play this video.

statement: Is ball A a cause of ball E going through the goal?

stimulus:
You will now watch the video clip three more times and answer the following comprehension questions:

If ball A is removed, will ball E have gone through the gate?

If ball B is removed, will ball E have gone through the gate?
